sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Pod<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OSAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant JupyterServer as Jupyter Server<br/>localhost HTTP

    Note over User,JupyterServer: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Workbench

    User->>Router: GET https://{notebook}.apps.{cluster}/<br/>Browser request
    Router->>OAuth: Forward to 8443/TCP<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuth->>OSAuth: Validate OAuth2 token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    OSAuth-->>OAuth: Token valid<br/>User authorized
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888 (no encryption)
    Jupyter->>JupyterServer: Process request<br/>localhost (session token)
    JupyterServer-->>Jupyter: JupyterLab UI response
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: HTTP response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: JupyterLab interface

    Note over User,JupyterServer: Flow 2: Pipeline Runtime Executes Task

    participant KFPCtrl as KFP Controller
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RuntimePod as Runtime Pod
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    KFPCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Pod for pipeline task<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>RuntimePod: Pod created<br/>(runtime image)
    RuntimePod->>S3: Download data/model<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM/Secret Key
    S3-->>RuntimePod: Data artifacts
    RuntimePod->>RuntimePod: Execute pipeline task<br/>(Python code)
    RuntimePod->>K8sAPI: Upload results<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    RuntimePod-->>KFPCtrl: Task complete

    Note over User,JupyterServer: Flow 3: Image Build and Publish (Konflux)

    participant GitHub as GitHub
    participant KonfluxListener as Konflux EventListener<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Tekton as Tekton PipelineRun
    participant UBIRegistry as UBI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Quay as quay.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Scanner as Vulnerability Scanner<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    GitHub->>KonfluxListener: Webhook: code push<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Webhook Secret
    KonfluxListener->>Tekton: Trigger PipelineRun
    Tekton->>GitHub: Clone repository<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>GitHub Token
    Tekton->>UBIRegistry: Pull base images<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull Secret
    Tekton->>Tekton: Build container image<br/>buildah
    Tekton->>Scanner: Scan for CVEs<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>API Token
    Scanner-->>Tekton: CVE report (pass)
    Tekton->>Quay: Push signed image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Push Token (Cosign)
    Quay-->>Tekton: Image published
